Data from Henn et al, PNAS, 2015.
Distance from sub-Saharan Africa predicts mutational
load in diverse human genomes.
www.pnas.org/cgi/doi/10.1073/pnas.1510805112

Discarded sites with missing data, and focused on San and Maya individuals.

Assumed that 44Mb were sequenced without error, as the data was generated with an exome capture array, targeted at 44Mb.

Assumed a mutation rate of 1.4e-8 per site/per generation.
